{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:proverbs.5",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 5 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:1",
      "text": "My son, pay attention to my wisdom. Turn your ear to my understanding,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:2",
      "text": "that you may maintain discretion, that your lips may preserve knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:3",
      "text": "For the lips of an adulteress drip honey. Her mouth is smoother than oil,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:4",
      "text": "but in the end she is as bitter as wormwood, and as sharp as a two-edged sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:5",
      "text": "Her feet go down to death. Her steps lead straight to Sheol.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:6",
      "text": "She gives no thought to the way of life. Her ways are crooked, and she doesn’t know it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:7",
      "text": "Now therefore, my sons, listen to me. Don’t depart from the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:8",
      "text": "Remove your way far from her. Don’t come near the door of her house,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:9",
      "text": "lest you give your honor to others, and your years to the cruel one;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:10",
      "text": "lest strangers feast on your wealth, and your labors enrich another man’s house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:11",
      "text": "You will groan at your latter end, when your flesh and your body are consumed,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:12",
      "text": "and say, “How I have hated instruction, and my heart despised reproof.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:13",
      "text": "I haven’t obeyed the voice of my teachers, nor turned my ear to those who instructed me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:14",
      "text": "I have come to the brink of utter ruin, among the gathered assembly.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:15",
      "text": "Drink water out of your own cistern, running water out of your own well.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:16",
      "text": "Should your springs overflow in the streets, streams of water in the public squares?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:17",
      "text": "Let them be for yourself alone, not for strangers with you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:18",
      "text": "Let your spring be blessed. Rejoice in the wife of your youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:19",
      "text": "A loving doe and a graceful deer — let her breasts satisfy you at all times. Be captivated always with her love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:20",
      "text": "For why should you, my son, be captivated with an adulteress? Why embrace the bosom of another?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:21",
      "text": "For the ways of man are before Yahweh’s eyes. He examines all his paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:22",
      "text": "The evil deeds of the wicked ensnare him. The cords of his sin hold him firmly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:proverbs.5.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 5:23",
      "text": "He will die for lack of instruction. In the greatness of his folly, he will go astray.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
